    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**8 files** to touch across the full stack:\n\n### New files\n- **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — iterates `CacheBucket::iter()` + `Python`, calls `DiskUsage::new(vec![bucket_path]).count_ignoring_errors()` for each, prints a padded two-column table (name | size) then a separator and total. Mirrors the `--human` flag from `cache_size`.\n- **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** — 3 integration tests: empty cache, raw bytes, human-readable.\n\n### Modified files\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` feature flag + `\"cache-stats\"` string mappings.\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand`; add `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`).\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` + `mod cache_stats;`.\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — One new match arm dispatching `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` → `commands::cache_stats(...)`.\n5. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command builder and `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter.\n6. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Register `#[cfg(all(feature = \"test-python\", feature = \"test-pypi\"))] mod cache_stats;`.\n\n### Key design note\n`CacheBucket::to_str()` is private to `uv-cache`. Since `cache_stats` lives in the `uv` crate, use `format!(\"{bucket}\")` (via the public `Display` impl) for bucket names instead of calling `to_str()` directly. The `Python` bucket is excluded from `CacheBucket::iter()` but should appear in stats, so it's appended via `.chain(std::iter::once(CacheBucket::Python))`.",
